The ongoing three-day national convention of the National Association of Nigerian Students (NANS) was on Thursday disrupted by violence.About 20 members of the association, who gathered at the old parade ground in Abuja for the convention, sustained wounds from gunshots and machete after thugs loyal to a factional coordinator of the association in Zone D (Southwest) began attacking delegates.  See Also






